Kamchatka, Russia Climate

Weather: 8.88°C/47.98°F, Wind SW at 3.11 km/h, 90% Humidity, 0% Chance of rain

Kamchatka Climate Summary

Located at an elevation of 505.15 meters (1657.32 feet) above sea level, Kamchatka has a Subartic, severe winter, no dry season, cool summer climate (Classification: Dfc). The city’s yearly temperature is -2.72ºC (27.1ºF) and it is -7.99% lower than Russia’s averages. Kamchatka typically receives about 99.78 millimeters (3.93 inches) of precipitation and has 189.11 rainy days (51.81% of the time) annually.
